Package org.spongepowered.api.data.manipulators

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AttributeData
    Represents an item data that deals specifically with an item stack granting AttributeModifiers.
    ColoredData
    Represents item data that uses colors.
    CommandData
    Represents all mutable data associated with a CommandBlock.
    DisplayNameData
    Represents the display name of an ItemStack, Entity, or TileEntity.
    DyeableData  
    FireworkData
    Represents data specific to fireworks.
    IntData<T extends IntData<T>>  
    ListData<E,T extends ListData<E,T>>
    Represents an item that can have a Collection of types of elements.
    MappedData<K,V,T extends MappedData<K,V,T>>
    Represents item data that is mapped by a specific key and value type definition.
    MobSpawnerData
    Represents the data associated with a mob spawner, including the spawn delay, the spawn count, and the list of possible entities that can be spawned.
    OwnableData
    Represents data pertaining to a GameProfile that is marked as "owning" the DataHolder.
    PotionEffectData  
    SingleValueData<V,T extends SingleValueData<V,T>>
    Represents a DataManipulator that handles a single value with default provided methods to SingleValueData.getValue() and SingleValueData.setValue(Object).
    TargetedLocationData  
    WetData
    Signifies that a DataHolder is currently "wet".
